| **Barratry Act 1471** (repealed) | May 1471 c. 4 [a] c. 43 [e] | 6 May 1471 | *That na clerkis purches abbasyis and uthir beneficis at the court of Rome quhilkis was nocht thairat of befor—nor offices of collectory—nor unyownys and annexacionis of benefices.*<br>That no cleric purchase abbeys and other benefices at the court of Rome, which was not thereof before; nor offices of collectory; nor unions and annexations of benefices. (Repealed by [Statute Law Revision (Scotland) Act 1906](/Statute_Law_Revision_(Scotland)_Act_1906) ([6 Edw. 7](/6_Edw._7). c. 38)) |
